{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0179LY4FE3uhFPSa7GjcBtuN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: TypeScript Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-04-24\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public TypeScript surface for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/ts/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# TypeScript Interface\n11\t\n12\tThis file owns TypeScript-visible symbol spelling and export shape. Cross-\n13\tbinding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n14\t\n15\t## Runtime surface\n16\t\n17\tThe canonical runtime verbs available to TypeScript callers are:\n18\t\n19\t- `Engine.open(...)`\n20\t- `engine.write(...)`\n21\t- `engine.search(...)`\n22\t- `engine.close()`\n23\t- `admin.configure(...)`\n24\t\n25\tAll runtime operations are Promise-returning on the TS surface.\n26\t\n27\t`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\n28\towned by `design/engine.md`.\n29\t\n30\t`Engine.open(path, options?)` accepts an options object with an `engineConfig`\n31\tmember carrying the engine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in camelCase:\n32\t\n33\t- `embedderPoolSize`\n34\t- `schedulerRuntimeThreads`\n35\t- `provenanceRowCap`\n36\t- `embedderCallTimeoutMs`\n37\t- `slowThresholdMs`\n38\t\n39\tIf TypeScript exposes ThreadsafeFunction handoff-pool sizing, that option is a\n40\tTS binding-runtime option beside `engineConfig`, not a canonical engine config\n41\tfield and not a Python parity obligation.\n42\t\n43\t## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n44\t\n45\tThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n46\t\n47\t- `engine.drain(timeoutMs)`\n48\t- `engine.counters()`\n49\t- `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`\n50\t- `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`\n51\t\n52\tSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n53\t\n54\t- `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })`\n55\t\n56\t`callback` receives the stable `fathomdb` payload described in\n57\t`design/bindings.md`.\n58\t\n59\t## Caller-visible data shapes\n60\t\n61\t- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n62\t- `SearchResult.projectionCursor`\n63\t- `SearchResult.softFallback.branch`\n64\t\n65\t`softFallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n66\t\n67\t## Errors\n68\t\n69\tTypeScript exposes one concrete leaf class per canonical row in\n70\t`design/errors.md`.\n71\t\n72\tLeaf-class examples:\n73\t\n74\t- `DatabaseLockedError`\n75\t- `CorruptionError`\n76\t- `MigrationError`\n77\t- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n78\t- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n79\t- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n80\t- `SchemaValidationError`\n81\t- `OverloadedError`\n82\t- `ClosingError`\n83\t\n84\tTypeScript exports one catch-all base class, `FathomDbError`, and every\n85\tconcrete leaf class in the `design/errors.md` matrix extends it. Open-time and\n86\truntime leaf classes remain distinct, but callers can catch `FathomDbError`\n87\tfor both.\n88\t\n89\t## Non-presence\n90\t\n91\tTypeScript does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\n92\tthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `checkIntegrity`, `quick`, `full`, or\n93\t`roundTrip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n94\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e03e003f-16a4-48ce-9857-522e8e7e136e","uuid":"656684c0-edb0-4701-bca3-2a724e821ecd","timestamp":"2026-05-17T20:44:48.408Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-TX-ts-python-parity-20260517T204414Z/dev/interfaces/typescript.md","content":"---\ntitle: TypeScript Public Interface\ndate: 2026-04-24\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public TypeScript surface for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/ts/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# TypeScript Interface\n\nThis file owns TypeScript-visible symbol spelling and export shape. Cross-\nbinding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Runtime surface\n\nThe canonical runtime verbs available to TypeScript callers are:\n\n- `Engine.open(...)`\n- `engine.write(...)`\n- `engine.search(...)`\n- `engine.close()`\n- `admin.configure(...)`\n\nAll runtime operations are Promise-returning on the TS surface.\n\n`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\nowned by `design/engine.md`.\n\n`Engine.open(path, options?)` accepts an options object with an `engineConfig`\nmember carrying the engine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in camelCase:\n\n- `embedderPoolSize`\n- `schedulerRuntimeThreads`\n- `provenanceRowCap`\n- `embedderCallTimeoutMs`\n- `slowThresholdMs`\n\nIf TypeScript exposes ThreadsafeFunction handoff-pool sizing, that option is a\nTS binding-runtime option beside `engineConfig`, not a canonical engine config\nfield and not a Python parity obligation.\n\n## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n\nThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n\n- `engine.drain(timeoutMs)`\n- `engine.counters()`\n- `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`\n- `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`\n\nSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n\n- `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })`\n\n`callback` receives the stable `fathomdb` payload described in\n`design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Caller-visible data shapes\n\n- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n- `SearchResult.projectionCursor`\n- `SearchResult.softFallback.branch`\n\n`softFallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n\n## Errors\n\nTypeScript exposes one concrete leaf class per canonical row in\n`design/errors.md`.\n\nLeaf-class examples:\n\n- `DatabaseLockedError`\n- `CorruptionError`\n- `MigrationError`\n- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n- `SchemaValidationError`\n- `OverloadedError`\n- `ClosingError`\n\nTypeScript exports one catch-all base class, `FathomDbError`, and every\nconcrete leaf class in the `design/errors.md` matrix extends it. Open-time and\nruntime leaf classes remain distinct, but callers can catch `FathomDbError`\nfor both.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nTypeScript does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\nthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `checkIntegrity`, `quick`, `full`, or\n`roundTrip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n","numLines":94,"startLine":1,"totalLines":94}}}
